  "body": "`now := dbtime.Now()` used for synthetic test data can land before the\nreal jobs' DB-assigned `CreatedAt` when NTP steps the clock backwards.\nThis shifts UUID index assignments in `updateReplaceUUIDs` and breaks\ngolden file comparisons.\n\nConfirmed via [CI logs](https://github.com/coder/coder/actions/runs/22529771802)\nshowing a ~1.9s clock regression on macOS during `completeWorkspaceBuildJob`.\n\nFix: derive synthetic timestamps from the latest real job's `CreatedAt`\ninstead of the wall clock, which makes this much less likely. Also add\nstable sort tiebreakers and job success assertions for debuggability.\n\nFixes coder/internal#449\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with [Coder Mux](https://mux.coder.com)",
  "changed_files": 1,
